QUESTION STATEMENT - 8
Why is eggs a valid variable name while 100 is invalid?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 8
VARIABLE NAME CAN ONLY START WITH ANY ALPHABET (CAPITAL OR SMALL) OR UNDERSCORE SO, BECAUSE OF THIS EGGS IS A VALID VARIABLE
WHILE 100 IS NOT A VALID VARIABLE BECAUSE WE CANNOT NAME A VARIABLE OTHER THAN ALPHABET AND UNDERSCORE ONLY.


QUESTION STATEMENT - 9
What three functions can be used to get the integer, floating-point number, or string
version of a value?

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 9
FOR INTEGER WE CAN USE (INT), FOR FLOATING-POINT NUMBER WE CAN USE (FLOAT), FOR STRING WE CAN USE (STR)


QUESTION STATEMENT - 10
Why does this expression cause an error? How can you fix it?
'I have eaten'  + 99 +  'burritos.'

SOLUTION STATEMENT - 10
THIS EXPRESSION CAUSE ERROR BECAUSE WE CANNONT DIRECTLY CANCATINATE STRING AND INTEGER HERE WE HAVE TWO STRINGS AND ONE INTEGER VALUE SO IN ORDER TO DEBUG THIS STATEMENT WE NEED TO PUT 99 IN SINGLE QUOTES OR DOUBLE QUOTES ('99') AFTER DOING THIS WE CAN EASILY CONCATINATE THE ABOVE STRING AND FINAL RESULT WILL BE LIKE ' HAVE EATEN 99 BURRITOS'